This 450 Marlin ammunition is safe and is designed for use in ANY/ALL 450 Marlin firearms in normal operating condition.

We always use factory stock firearms to determine our published velocities, so you get true, actual field velocities with our ammo -- not exaggerated long laboratory test barrel velocities.

1.     Item 22A (430gr. Hard Cast Penetrator)

1901 fps Marlin 22 inch barrel
1860 fps Marlin 18.5 inch barrel
2.     Item 22B (405gr. JFN Expander)

1974 fps Marlin 22 inch barrel
1930 fps Marlin 18.5 inch barrel 
3.     Item 22C (500gr. FMJ-FN Barnes Buster Penetrator)

1600 fps Marlin 22 inch barrel
1558 fps Marlin 18.5 inch barrel


You'll note that these 450 Marlin loads are generating slightly lower velocities than their 45-70 counterparts. This is because the 450 Marlin brass (as made by Hornady) has a heavier web  and as such the powder capacity was lessened, so the amount of propellant we can fit into the case is slightly less than with Starline 45-70 brass.

Item 22A -- utilizes a flat nosed hard cast non-expanding bullet that will penetrate 5 to 6 straight line feet in muscle and bone.

Item 22B -- utilizes a bullet that expands to an inch or more at our velocities and hence penetration is limited to about two feet in flesh and bone. This is the single most effective hog and black bear load ever devised in 450 Marlin. I won't use it on animals weighing over 800 lbs as it won't give adequate penetration at bad angles for animals for animals over 800 lbs. If you'll limit yourself to broadside (double lung) and CNS hits, this load will work on animals up to 2,000 lbs.

Item 22C -- utilizes a FMJ-FN bullet designed to penetrate 5 to 6 feet in flesh and bone.

title: For Sale:  M1101 HUMMWV Trailer, Like New
postcontent:
I have one M1101 US ARMY HUMMWV trailer for sale. This is the most insanely overbuilt trailer in the history of mankind! This thing rides on 37" Goodyear runflats and has a 16 inches of ground clearance (just like the HUMMWV). On top of that, it can hold (according the the data plate) 1940 Lbs in the bed....yeah right! The M1102 trailer, which is IDENTICAL (except for the data plate) is listed as being abale to carry a payload of 2740 Lbs. So, this thing can, in reality, carry at least that much. The military also states their ratings as the off-road rating, which is always half of the on road capacity. Loading it above what the data plate states is at your own risk, but when you see this thing, you'll realize it can haul a house.

The condition of the trailer is REMARKABLE! It's all aluminum bed is in amazing shape, and may never have been issued (it certainly wasn't shipped to a combat zone and abused). All of the parts are there, including the rear landing legs. The jerry can holder is attached and all the lights work. I have converted the tail lights to 12V (just changed out the bulbs) and have replaced the 12-pin military connector with a standard 4-pin connector. The wiring is still all there if you have a military truck and need the 12-pin plug. Has surge brakes that help a ton when carrying a heavy load. The trailer itself only weighs 1460 Lbs!

title: For Sale/Trade:  Lone eagle ssp-91 223
postcontent: For sale is an ssp-91 also known as the lone eagle by magnum research. It is in .223 caliber so if you have an AR-15 you need this. It comes with a Burris 2-7 handgun scope which by itself is worth $300. It will shoot great groups up to 200 yards at least. It is in very nice shape with some scratches and dings as you would expect. If you have never shot a rifle caliber handgun they are a ton of fun and not that bad with recoil. This one has the canon type breech load that centers the barrel nicely.  It is now on consignment at RSM firearms in Belvidere if you would like to see and handle it.
